    "created_at": "2016-08-10T11:41:39Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-08-10T11:41:39Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "@willingc thanks!\n\nI found something that works: #9854. It notices when `NSApp:run` finishes without having triggered the callback on the inputhook FD, and then continues the lower-level eventloop instead of returning. This appears to be because closing the last Window triggers NSApp:stop, but doesn't (for some reason that I don't understand) finish processing the events necessary to actually close that Window.\n\nI also tried running CFRunLoop directly instead of invoking NSApp ever, but this doesn't seem to get the GUI events necessary to interact with the Windows.\n\nI'm pretty confident there's a better way to do it, but I don't know what it is and this works, so I'm okay with it.\n"
  },
