    "body": "This problem seemed solved to me sometime around when this issue closed in August, though I can't remember precisely. However, as for @nirum, it has reappeared recently, again I can't say if it corresponded to a particular update.\n\nThe scope seems to be a little smaller now. Figures close normally in the GUI interface when I press `⌘w` (`<CMD-W>`) or click the close window button `ⓧ`. The window disappears, and the figure is no longer listed in `plt.get_fignums()`.\n\nHowever, if I run `plt.close` (with any argument, as long as it ends up closing all figures), then all the figures remain open (i.e., visible in the GUI) but they're grey and frozen (trying to interact via the GUI gives the spinning beach ball). After this, `plt.get_fignums()` returns an empty list.\n\nCreating a new figure closes the frozen figure(s) and proceeds as normal. Running `plt.draw()` also closes them, and creates a single empty figure.\n\nHere's my system currently in case it helps:\n\n```\nOS X El Capitan 10.11.6\niTerm2 Build 3.0.11\nPython 2.7.12           (homebrew)\nIPython 5.1.0           (pip)\nmatplotlib 1.5.3        (pip)\n\nIPython.sys_info()\n{'commit_hash': u'5c9c918', 'commit_source': 'installation',\n 'default_encoding': 'UTF-8', 'platform': 'Darwin-15.6.0-x86_64-i386-64bit',\n 'ipython_path': '/usr/local/lib/python2.7/site-packages/IPython',\n 'ipython_version': '5.1.0', 'os_name': 'posix', 'sys_platform': 'darwin',\n 'sys_executable': '/usr/local/opt/python/bin/python2.7',\n 'sys_version': '2.7.12 (default, Oct 11 2016, 05:24:00) \\n[GCC 4.2.1 Compatible Apple LLVM 8.0.0 (clang-800.0.38)]'}\n```\n"
  },
